The paper discusses the optimization techniques of Bloom filters, which are commonly used in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB) for membership query. The paper also mentions the importance of reducing false positives, which is a security concern and falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the functionality of Bloom filters, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
